      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The civil rights movement in the US was a pivotal moment in American history, marked by courageous acts of defiance against systemic racism. The movement began with the Montgomery Bus Boycott (1955-1956), led by Dr. Martin Luther King Jr., in response to Rosa Parks' arrest. The March on Washington (1963) and the Selma to Montgomery Marches (1965) brought national attention to the cause, culminating in the passage of landmark legislation like the Civil Rights Act (1964) and Voting Rights Act (1965). The movement's momentum continued with the Black Power movement and the assassinations of key figures like Martin Luther King Jr. and Malcolm X.",
